cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.SOC, cs.IR, cs.CL 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as it deals with identifying communities of users on Twitter based on their shared interests. It also involves the use of multivariate time series analysis, which is a common technique used in social network analysis. 

It could also belong to cs.SD (Software Development and Programming) as it involves the development of a method for identifying communities on Twitter. 

cs.SOC (Social and Economic Networks) is another possible sub-category as the paper deals with social networks and communities of users. 

cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also a possible sub-category as the paper involves the identification of topics from Twitter data. 

Finally, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is a possible sub-category as the paper involves the use of natural language processing techniques to identify topics from tweets.
